<br>
There are many quests in DAoC where you sit there waiting for something to spawn; same as in Everquest.<br>
<br>
I don't see the difference. <p>Tuan {Cupcakes} the Vicar</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uarikel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arikel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1943<br> <font color=#E9D756>(11/26/01 1:19:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yea, he's pretty big...</span><hr size=1> That's not as common in DAoC, at least not in Hibernia, and the camp times seem to be much, much shorter.  I recently read a post on the web describing a 1 hour camp as particularly long.  Imagine someone making a statement like that about an Everquest camp.  It'd be considered ridiculous. <p>Ahry - hero of Gaoth an Iar, Percival server <BR>
